  "text": "# Apache Flink Windowing API Extension Points\n\n## 1. WindowAssigner Abstract Base Class\n**Location:** `github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/WindowAssigner.java`\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class WindowAssigner<T, W extends Window>`\n\n**Abstract Methods (Extension Points):**\n- `public abstract Collection<W> assignWindows(T element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context)` - Assigns zero or more windows to an element based on its timestamp and a context that provides current processing time.\n- `public abstract Trigger<T, W> getDefaultTrigger()` - Returns the default trigger associated with this assigner. Developers can customize trigger behavior for their windowing strategy.\n- `public abstract TypeSerializer<W> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)` - Provides a serializer for the specific window type produced by this assigner.\n- `public abstract boolean isEventTime()` - Indicates whether windows are based on event time (true) or processing time (false).\n\n**Inner Class:** `WindowAssignerContext` with method `getCurrentProcessingTime()` for querying current system time.\n\n## 2. MergingWindowAssigner Subclass\n**Location:** `github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/MergingWindowAssigner.java`\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class MergingWindowAssigner<T, W extends Window> extends WindowAssigner<T, W>`\n\n**Extension Point for Merging:**\n- `public abstract void mergeWindows(Collection<W> windows, MergeCallback<W> callback)` - Determines which windows should be merged. This is the critical extension point for session-style windows where overlapping or adjacent windows must be combined.\n\n**Callback Interface:** `MergeCallback<W>` with method `void merge(Collection<W> toBeMerged, W mergeResult)` for specifying merge results.\n\n## 3. Trigger Base Class (Lifecycle Methods)\n**Location:** `github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/triggers/Trigger.java`\n\n**Class:** `public abstract class Trigger<T, W extends Window>`\n\n**Lifecycle Methods (Extension Points):**\n- `public abstract TriggerResult onElement(T element, long timestamp, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when an element arrives in a window pane. Determines whether the pane should be evaluated.\n- `public abstract TriggerResult onProcessingTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when a processing-time timer fires. Allows triggers based on wall-clock time.\n- `public abstract TriggerResult onEventTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when an event-time timer fires based on watermarks. Enables event-driven triggering.\n- `public abstract void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Clears trigger state when a window is purged, including timers.\n\n**Merge Support Methods:**\n- `public boolean canMerge()` - Returns true if the trigger supports window merging (default: false). Must be true for use with MergingWindowAssigner.\n- `public void onMerge(W window, OnMergeContext ctx)` - Called when windows are merged. Implementations must properly handle trigger state merging.\n\n**Context Interfaces:**\n- `TriggerContext` - Provides access to timer registration, watermarks, metrics, and per-window state.\n- `OnMergeContext extends TriggerContext` - Extended context for merge operations, with `mergePartitionedState()` method.\n\n## 4. Reference Implementation: EventTimeSessionWindows\n**Location:** `github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/EventTimeSessionWindows.java`\n\n**Class:** `public class EventTimeSessionWindows extends MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>`\n\n**Implementation Pattern:**\n\n**assignWindows() Implementation:**\n```java\npublic Collection<TimeWindow> assignWindows(Object element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context) {\n    return Collections.singletonList(new TimeWindow(timestamp, timestamp + sessionTimeout));\n}\n```\nCreates a single TimeWindow starting at the element's timestamp and extending by the session gap/timeout.\n\n**mergeWindows() Implementation:**\n```java\npublic void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c) {\n    TimeWindow.mergeWindows(windows, c);\n}\n```\nDelegates to the static `TimeWindow.mergeWindows()` method which handles overlap detection and merging of overlapping session windows.\n\n**Other Methods:**\n- `getDefaultTrigger()` returns `EventTimeTrigger.create()` - Triggers are fired based on event time progress (watermarks).\n- `isEventTime()` returns true - Session windows are based on element timestamps, not processing time.\n- `getWindowSerializer()` returns `new TimeWindow.Serializer()` - Uses TimeWindow's standard serialization.\n\n## 5. TimeWindow Class (Window Type)\n**Location:** `github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java`\n\n**Class:** `public class TimeWindow extends Window`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `private final long start` - Window start time (inclusive).\n- `private final long end` - Window end time (exclusive).\n\n**Constructor:**\n- `public TimeWindow(long start, long end)` - Creates a time window for the given timestamp range.\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `public static void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` - Static utility method used by session window assigners to merge overlapping TimeWindows. This is the core merging logic: windows are sorted, and overlapping windows are identified and merged into larger windows.\n- `public TimeWindow cover(TimeWindow other)` - Returns the minimal window covering both this and another window, used internally for merge results.\n\n**Inner Class:**\n- `public static class Serializer extends TypeSerializerSingleton<TimeWindow>` - Handles serialization/deserialization of TimeWindow objects for checkpointing and state backend storage.\n\n## Extension Point Summary\nA developer implementing a custom window assigner must:\n1. Extend `WindowAssigner` and implement `assignWindows()`, `getDefaultTrigger()`, `getWindowSerializer()`, and `isEventTime()`.\n2. For merging windows (like sessions), extend `MergingWindowAssigner` and implement `mergeWindows()`.\n3. Optionally implement a custom `Trigger` by extending `Trigger` and implementing all lifecycle methods: `onElement()`, `onProcessingTime()`, `onEventTime()`, and `clear()`. If using with a `MergingWindowAssigner`, also override `canMerge()` to return true and implement `onMerge()`.\n4. Choose or create a `Window` subclass (e.g., `TimeWindow`) to represent the window boundaries.\n\nThe EventTimeSessionWindows demonstrates this pattern: it assigns each element to a session window of the configured timeout duration, delegates merging to TimeWindow's utility method, and uses EventTimeTrigger for event-driven firing."
}

